parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag warning light illuminates
the airbag does not deploy in a crash
the passenger airbag is turned off
the driver's side airbag is replaced under recall but the passenger side is not.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in remedying the Takata airbag recall can lead to continued risk of injury or death due to faulty airbags.
symptoms: The contact receives notification of the recall but the parts are unavailable
the dealer does not have the parts
the contact is placed on a waiting list
the manufacturer exceeds a reasonable amount of time for the recall repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become stiff or difficult to turn, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels stiff or hard to turn
the steering wheel sticks or locks up
the vehicle is difficult to maneuver
especially at low speeds
and the power steering fluid level is low or leaking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column and rack can cause the steering wheel to become stuck or difficult to turn, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels stiff or hard to turn
the steering wheel sticks or locks up
the vehicle is difficult to maneuver
especially at low speeds
and abnormal noises are heard while turning.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Tie Rod and Ball Joint Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the tie rod and ball joint can cause the steering wheel to become loose or difficult to control, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels loose or wobbly
the vehicle is difficult to maneuver
especially at high speeds
and abnormal noises are heard while turning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle may shift into four-wheel drive or four-low mode without input from the driver, which can cause loss of control, accidents, or difficulty maneuvering.
symptoms: The transfer case shifts into four-wheel drive or four-low mode without input from the driver
the "Service 4WD" light illuminates
and the vehicle may vibrate or jerk when shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission may slip or fail, causing loss of power, vibration, or difficulty shifting gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips or fails
causing the vehicle to vibrate or jerk
difficulty shifting gears
and loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch slave cylinder can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
and difficulty shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various issues, including the horn sounding randomly, the window not functioning, and the compass and fuel economy display malfunctioning.
symptoms: The horn sounds randomly
the window does not function
the compass and fuel economy display malfunction
and other electrical system failures.
